f=Engineering/dev/custom/architecture-decisions/SKILL.md · in=architecture-decisions maintains department's ADR (Architecture Decision Record) ledger: significant technical choice recorded context, options weighed, decision, consequences append-only, superseded never deleted. Engineering's institutional memory *why system way is*, discipline precedent applies governance rulings. · p=Undocumented architecture rots folklore: nobody remembers queue chosen over cron, someone rips out reintroduces bug prevented. ADR ledger stops decisions carry their reasoning forward, reversing one requires confronting original context. · wu=Triggers: "architecture decision," "should use [X]," "why choose [Y]," "record ADR," before any choice expensive reverse (framework, datastore, auth model, platform-level dependency like whether adopt HelixDB graph memory). · st:/ Protocol=`A significant choice arises \· -> Draft the ADR (assets/adr-template.md): context \· options \· decision \· consequences \· -> Review with the owning agents if it touches their domain \· (data → dana \· backend/API → raj \· frontend → mia \· mobile → nova \· security → aegis \· reliability → ops) \· -> Log to the ADR ledger (append-only); assign a number` · in=**Draft.** Context (the forces play, honestly), options actually considered (2+; "we thought one" itself finding), decision, consequences including ones don't like. fabricated alternatives look thorough. **Review domain.** decision touches another agent's domain, agent reviews before ADR logged cross-domain decisions made unilaterally integration breaks. **Log.** Append ledger (`assets/adr-ledger-template.md` one index row ADR) sequential zero-padded number (ADR-001…) date; numbers never reused, including rejected proposals. Status: proposed accepted rejected; accepted superseded-by ADR-NNN. **Supersede, never delete.** reversed decision becomes new ADR referencing old; old one's status flips superseded-by. history value. · of=completed ADR (per template) ledger entry. Reversal produces new numbered ADR. · pr=**Every significant decision recorded reasoning.** "We decided because highest-value sentence system., **Two options minimum, honestly weighed** decision record one option rationalization., **Consequences include downsides** ADR lists benefits marketing., **Append-only; supersede, never delete** (precedent's discipline)., **Cross-domain decisions get cross-domain review** before logging., **Charter-bound**: ADR cannot decide weaken Security Charter rail operator amendment, architecture decision. · f=Ledger doesn't exist skill starts `assets/adr-ledger-template.md` first ADR., Decision already made without ADR backfill one, labeled reconstructed, future readers least reasoning best recalled., Reviewer disagrees disagreement recorded ADR's consequences; unresolved high-stakes splits escalate operator (dev recommends, doesn't overrule domain owners). · b:with Other Skills=`stack-profile` (sibling) records *current* stack; ADRs record *why* it's stack change it. stack change ADR., `code-review-standards` enforces decisions time; ADRs make them., Cross-department: platform-level decisions (e.g., toongine's graph-memory datastore) ADRs reviewed marcus/board they carry strategic spend weight.